Saw III
6.2
AdvertisementBy JEANNETTE CATSOULISThe Since Jigsaw is currently laid low by a brain tumor, his torture-as- therapy program requires the assistance of Amanda (Shawnee Smith), a  sidekick who slices her own thighs when no one else’s are handy. Amanda probably spent a lot of time in her teens writing to men on death row.Having learned the (knotted) ropes on The most depressing thing about this series is not the creativity of the bloodletting but the bleak view of human nature, specifically our talent for ruining the present to avenge the past. In the opening scene, a man frees himself from an ankle restraint by pulverizing his foot with a brick; fortunately, all we have to do is get up and leave. “Saw III” is rated R (Under 17 requires accompanying parent or adult guardian). It is obscene in every regard.





